var __index = {"config":{"lang":["en"],"separator":"[\\s\\-]+","pipeline":["stopWordFilter"]},"docs":[{"location":"index.html","title":"Welcome to ReadShade","text":""},{"location":"index.html#offline-download","title":"Offline Download","text":"<p>https://github.com/papadanku/ReadShade/archive/refs/heads/gh-pages.zip</p>"},{"location":"index.html#building-instructions","title":"Building Instructions","text":"<ul> <li><code>mkdocs serve</code> - Start the live-reloading docs server.</li> <li><code>mkdocs build</code> - Build the documentation site.</li> <li><code>mkdocs -h</code> - Print help message and exit.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"index.html#project-layout","title":"Project Layout","text":"<pre><code>mkdocs.yml    # The configuration file.\ndocs/\n    index.md  # The documentation homepage.\n    ...       # Other markdown pages, images and other files.\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/dlssframegen.html","title":"Disabling DLSS Frame Generation","text":"<p>This Guide will Focus on two methods of disabling DLSS Frame Generation so you don't crash when starting/playing your game.</p> <p>The first method I will show you will disable it in all games on Windows.</p>"},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/dlssframegen.html#instructions","title":"Instructions","text":"<ol> <li> <p>Go to <code>Display Settings</code>.</p> <p></p> </li> <li> <p>Next, go to <code>System &gt; Display &gt; Graphics</code> and click on <code>Change default  graphics settings</code>.</p> <p></p> </li> <li> <p>After you click on this you want to look for <code>Hardware Accelerated GPU Scheduling</code></p> <p></p> </li> <li> <p>Turn off <code>Hardware Accelerated GPU Scheduling</code></p> <p></p> </li> <li> <p>Reset your PC and it should globally disable Frame Generation.</p> </li> </ol>"},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/dlssframegen.html#demonstration-ghost-runner-2","title":"Demonstration: Ghost Runner 2","text":"<p>Will be use for this demonstration. For disabling it on a game individually. Most games will be similar.</p> <p></p>"},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/dlssframegen.html#instructions_1","title":"Instructions","text":"<ol> <li> <p>You will be looking for a file called: <code>nvngx_dlssg.dll</code></p> <p>In this case it's in the Streamline folder:</p> <p></p> </li> <li> <p>In this case all you need to do is rename <code>nvngx_dlssg.dll</code> to <code>nvngx_dlssg.back</code></p> <p></p> </li> </ol>"},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/dlssframegen.html#conclusion","title":"Conclusion","text":"<p>That should be it for now. I will post more examples for other game later. Good luck.</p>"},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/genericdepth.html","title":"Generic Depth","text":""},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/genericdepth.html#preface","title":"Preface","text":"<p>Okay, let's talk about the basics. You will need the add-on version of ReShade. Read it here.</p> <p>Then you will need to download the add-on it self here.</p> <p>Make sure you use the correct one for your game.</p>"},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/posteffects.html","title":"Deleting Post Effects on Unreal Engine","text":"<p>Depending on the game a few things can be done.</p>"},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/posteffects.html#unreal-engine-4","title":"Unreal Engine 4","text":"<ul> <li>Motion Blur</li> <li>Depth of Field</li> <li>Chromatic Abberation</li> </ul>"},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/posteffects.html#phase-1","title":"Phase 1","text":"<ol> <li> <p>Head over to <code>%APPDATA%</code> or <code>%LOCALAPPDATA%</code></p> <ul> <li> <p>Steam</p> <p><code>`\"GAME\"\\Saved\\Config\\WindowsNoEditor</code></p> </li> <li> <p>Windows Game Store</p> <p><code>\"GAME\"\\Saved\\Config\\WinGDK</code></p> </li> </ul> </li> <li> <p>Open the <code>Engine.ini</code> file and at the bottom of the file. Add:</p> <p><code>[SystemSettings] r.DepthOfFieldQuality=0 r.MotionBlur.Max=0 r.MotionBlurQuality=0 r.DefaultFeature.MotionBlur=0 r.SceneColorFringe.Max=0 r.SceneColorFringeQuality=0</code></p> </li> <li> <p>Save the file and set it to <code>Read Only</code>.</p> </li> </ol> <p>There are other effects you can disable and control here. But, this guide only to get you going.</p> <p>Keep in mind if you change your setting in game you may need to restart so that this INI can remove the problem Post Effects.</p> <p>Also understand this may not always work in every instance.</p> <p>A good source for modding this INI is https://www.pcgamingwiki.com/</p>"},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/posteffects.html#unreal-engine-5","title":"Unreal Engine 5","text":"<p>Please Note Unreal Engine 5 Needs Different Settings.</p> <p>HellBlade 2:</p> <pre><code>[SystemSettings]\nr.SceneColorFringeQuality=0\nr.Tonemapper.GrainQuantization=0\nr.Tonemapper.Quality=0\nr.NT.Lens.Distortion.Intensity=0\nr.NT.Lens.Distortion.Stretch=0\nr.NT.Lens.ChromaticAberration.Intensity=0\nr.NT.DOF.RotationalBokeh=0\nr.NT.DOF.NTBokehTransform=0\nr.FilmGrain=0\n</code></pre> <p>For letterboxing removal:</p> <pre><code>r.NT.AllowAspectRatioHorizontalExtension=0\nr.NT.EnableConstrainAspectRatio=0\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/posteffects.html#shader-toggler","title":"Shader Toggler","text":"<p>This ReShade Add-on is free and can disable certain effects that can cause issues with Depth3D.</p> <p>You can read more about it here.</p> <p>Video Guide coming soon\u2122\ufe0f</p>"},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/reshadeversions.html","title":"ReShade Versions and You","text":""},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/reshadeversions.html#so-what-version-of-reshade-should-you-use","title":"So what version of ReShade should you use?","text":"<p>Beats me... I am kidding. But, lets find out together.</p>"},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/reshadeversions.html#am-i-going-to-play-online-or-offline","title":"\"Am I going to play online or offline?\"","text":"<p>The reason for this question is we need to know what the best ReShade version for you.</p> <p>If it's a online game you want to use the add-on version. This version has Network Detection disabled.</p> <p>https://reshade.me/</p> <p>Scroll to the bottom of reshade.me and click the 2nd button.</p> <p>Keep in mind you may not want to do this all the time.</p> <p>In that case if you are playing a single player game then the normal version is ok to use. You also get it at the link above. Just click the first button this time.</p>"},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/reshadeversions.html#do-i-need-a-special-version-of-reshade-for-the-game","title":"\"Do I need a special version of ReShade for the game?\"","text":"<p>Well in this case you need to download it from a other location.</p> <p>For example, this version of ReShade was made to work for Dragons Dogma 2 along side the REFramework.</p> <p>The game is single player but, I need to use a add-on.</p> <p>In that case download the ReShade Version with add-on Support. You can get it here.</p> <p>This version support almost every add-on like the ones here.</p>"},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/reshadeversions.html#where-can-i-get-an-older-version-of-reshade","title":"\"Where can I get an older version of ReShade?\"","text":"<p>There are a few ways to do that. But, the two easy ways of doing this is downloading directly from ReShades own website. Let me show you how.</p> <ul> <li> <p>Use this like for ReShade version Current to 3.0.0</p> <p>https://reshade.me/downloads/ReShade_Setup_x.x.x.exe</p> </li> <li> <p>Use this like for ReShade version Current to 5.0.0 and Current.</p> <p>https://reshade.me/downloads/ReShade_Setup_6.1.1_Addon.exe</p> </li> </ul> <p>For example I want to download a specific version of ReShade. But, it's no longer on the website. This is where I'm going to have to use the second method.</p> <ul> <li> <p>This is the ReShade Repository</p> <p>https://www.mediafire.com/folder/8ar1jhh1809cl/ReShade_Repository</p> <p>https://mega.nz/#!5eRxTCLZ!DuHO3dqJgZU4TJ5WP9H-eAJVPOJvDFa3U6hyypQkt5A</p> </li> </ul>"},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/reshadeversions.html#note","title":"Note","text":"<p>This is needed to download ReShade version 4.4.2 for Fallout, NV Fallout 3 and The Elder Scrolls IV: Oblivion.</p> <p>There may be other games that needs this old version. But, one day I hope we can add support for the old games listed here in newer version of ReShade.</p>"},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/reshadeversions.html#i-want-to-play-elden-ring-its-an-online-game-with-eac-can-i-do-this","title":"\"I want to play Elden Ring. It's an online game with EAC. Can I do this?\"","text":"<p>Yes you can. Some EAC games let you play online with ReShade.</p> <p>Elden Ring is one of them where the Developers allows for ReShade to be used. In this case use the Add-on version of ReShade.</p> <p>But, Not every game will work like this. For example the game Lords of the Fallen will not let you launch with any version of ReShade. You will have to disable EAC if you want to use it.</p> <p>If you do disable EAC, just use the add-on version at that point.</p>"},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/rest.html","title":"Reshade Effect Shader Toggler (R.E.S.T)","text":"<p>Used to separate effects from the game and layer ReShade shader under the isolated element.</p> <p></p>"},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/rest.html#how-do-we-start","title":"\"How do we start?\"","text":"<p>Welp, we are going to need to download the add-on first.</p> <p>You can download it from here.</p>"},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/rest.html#what-with-the-multi-files-in-there-whats-going-on-where-am-i-what-year-is-it-do-i-need-all-the-bits","title":"\"What with the multi files in there? What's going on where am I? What year is it? Do I need all the bits?\"","text":"<p>Wow... Hang on there. So the contents of the release folder should be a few shaders the FX files.</p> <p>There s also a License and a README File inside that folder. Ignore them for now.</p> <p>Yes, you do need all the bits. Well, You really only need one of the <code>.addon#</code>. But, you could drag them both in the same area where the ReShade.dll is.</p> <p>But, for are case we are going to to focus on the 64 bit add-on.</p>"},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/rest.html#ok-stop-i-grabbed-that-reshadeeffectshadertoggleraddon64-where-do-i-put-it-again","title":"\"OK, Stop, I grabbed that ReshadeEffectShaderToggler.addon64 where do I put it again?\"","text":"<p>You place this add-on where you installed ReShade too. So look for the game folder and look for dxgi.dll in this case.</p> <p>Note: REST add-on can or may work for other api's. But, the support is spotty. So we are focusing on a simple game in the hopes that it will be more understandable.</p>"},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/rest.html#wait-what-game","title":"\"Wait, What game?\"","text":"<p>So in this guide I am going to focus on a game called, Wiz\u2299rdum.</p> <p>But, you can use REST in a lot of different games in the image use for the post. That is DaggerFall Unity.</p> <p>Your folder should look like this.</p> <p></p> <p>Record Scratch You must be wondering how you got here.</p> <p>Well, I assumed that you already have the game installed. Also assumed that you installed ReShade already. This is why the image looks like this.</p> <p>A Basic ReShade install guide will be added later and linked here.</p>"},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/rest.html#ok-my-files-look-like-this-in-the-game-what-should-i-do-now","title":"\"OK, my files look like this in the game what should I do now?\"","text":"<p>Now, you should be able to start the game. ReShade should load and the add-on should be on the Add-on Tab.</p> <p></p> <p>Click the little arrow to open the a add-on. Also make sure to close the other add-ons to make it cleaner looking.</p> <p>Ok now that you done that it should look like this:</p> <p></p> <p>Ok close the ReShade menu and go in to the game. So we can use the add-on when we find in game UI.</p> <p>The start of the game should be enough.</p>"},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/rest.html#now-what-i-am-at-the-start-of-the-game-and-i-have-control-what-do-i-do-now","title":"\"Now what? I am at the start of the game and I have control what do I do now?\"","text":"<p>Open up, ReShade and move it to the right and it should look like this:</p> <p></p> <p>I am going to incease the ReShade Text size to make it easier to read.</p> <p>Now you should click on <code>New</code>.</p> <p></p> <p>It should open up like this:</p> <p></p> <p>You can now click <code>1. Activate [x]</code> and then click <code>2. Edit</code>.</p> <p></p> <p>Go ahead any type something in to the <code>3. Name</code> under the edit group.</p> <p>Then you should make a <code>4. Shortcut.</code> Once that is done click <code>5. OK.</code></p> <p>The order should be:</p> <ol> <li>Activate</li> <li>Edit</li> <li>Name</li> <li>Shortcut</li> <li>OK</li> </ol> <p>Now lets move on to searching for the UI. This is where it get a little more strange since now a new Window opens once you press <code>Settings</code>.</p> <p>Go ahead any type something in to the <code>3</code>. <code>Name</code> under the edit group.</p> <p>Then you should make a <code>4. Shortcut</code>. Once that is done click <code>5. OK</code>.</p> <p>The order should be:</p> <ol> <li>Activate</li> <li>Edit</li> <li>Name</li> <li>Shortcut</li> <li>OK</li> </ol> <p>Now lets move on to searching for the UI. This is where it get a little more strange since now a new Window opens once you press <code>Settings</code>:</p> <p></p>"},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/rest.html#hold-up-there-i-want-to-get-superdepth3d-working-with-this-arent-you-not-missing-something","title":"\"Hold Up There. I want to get SuperDepth3D working with this aren't you not missing something?\"","text":"<p>Oh Ya! We are missing something. @#$% Ok ya, Open up the main menu and enable the 3D Shader.</p> <p>You don't need to do this if you are not using Side by Side or Top n Bottom.</p> <p>Now scroll down to the bottom of the shader and enable <code>REST_UI_MODE</code>:</p> <p></p> <p>Set  0  to  1  for REST_UI_MODE.</p> <p>OK, Now lets go back to to the Add-on Tab again and click. Settings.</p>"},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/rest.html#ok-now-i-got-a-other-window-what-do-i-do-now","title":"\"Ok, Now I got a other window what do I do now?\"","text":"<p>Well now, lets orientate our selves. It should look like this:</p> <p></p> <p>Ok now lets zoom in and let me mark out the order:</p> <p></p> <ol> <li>Click off <code>Apply all enabled techniques [ ]</code></li> <li> <p>Click and mark the 3D Shader. <code>[x]</code></p> <p></p> </li> </ol> <p>It should look like that now.</p> <p>Ok now lets focus on the 3rd part:</p> <p></p> <p>This is the list of active buffers. Now we need to pick one that Isolates UI. So lets click and find the one we are looking for.</p> <p>I found the buffer that seems to work for me. See how it only really the game and not the Weapon hand or UI in this game.</p> <p></p> <p>This is the correct one currently. So lets for with this by double clicking the hex value:</p> <p></p> <p>See how it shows up as yellow.</p> <p>Now we can close the window.</p>"},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/rest.html#ok-i-got-to-where-you-isolated-that-thingy-so-do-i-click-save-all-toggle-groups","title":"\"Ok, I got to where you isolated that thingy. So do I click \"Save all Toggle Groups?\"","text":"<p>Yes you do click <code>Save all Toggle Groups</code>:</p> <p></p> <p>Close ReShade and look around!</p> <p>You will notice a issue. In this 3D image. Can you tell me what it is?</p> <p></p> <p>I think I see it! Is it the center crosshair?</p> <p>Yes, the issue is the center crosshair. There are three ways to deal with it.</p> <p>The first way is to just check if the game allows you to remove it.</p> <p>So lets looks in the game settings.</p> <p></p> <p>Yep found it.</p> <p>Under <code>Video</code>, set it to <code>nothing</code>.</p>"},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/rest.html#other-ways","title":"Other Ways","text":"<p>The other two ways is to use the ShaderToggler.</p> <p>That, or modding the game to remove that texture. The last method is the hardest.</p>"},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/rest.html#umm-i-have-a-problem-and-it-only-seems-to-happen-in-side-by-side-and-top-n-bottom-but-my-cursor-to-click-on-things-and-aiming-are-all-over-the-place-can-i-you-fix-it","title":"\"Umm I have a problem and it only seems to happen in Side by Side and Top n Bottom. But, my cursor to click on things and aiming are all over the place can I you fix it?\"","text":"<p>Yes you are correct. There is a work around for this issue that plagues <code>SbS</code> and <code>TnB</code> formats.</p> <p>I need you to go back to the <code>Shader Settings</code> and look for <code>Cursor Adjustments</code>.</p> <p></p> <p>Cursor type is set to <code>Off</code> You should set it to the one you like for your game:</p> <p></p> <p>For this case I selected <code>Reticle</code>.</p> <p>You can use <code>Mouse 5</code> to switch layers. So when you click it, it can go to the main menu or back to the game.</p> <p>You will notice once you close ReShade it will move all around the screen. To fix this, hit escape and/or go to a in game menu. Then, it should work as it should.</p>"},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/rest.html#this-look-fine-but-the-map-is-kind-of-broken-on-the-edges-can-i-fix-that","title":"\"This look fine. But, the map is kind of broken on the edges. Can I fix that?\"","text":"<p>Yes, you can. But, I will leave this up to you:</p> <p></p> <p>It's not really Needed. But, doing it makes it look nice.</p>"},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/rest.html#this-worked-for-this-game-but-what-if-i-want-to-share-this-with-other-people","title":"\"This worked for this game. But, what if I want to share this with other people?\"","text":"<p>You know when you clicked, <code>Save all Toggle Groups</code>.</p> <p>Well that generates a file in the same folder where the add-on is.</p> <p>It will be called  <code>ReshadeEffectShaderToggler.ini</code></p> <p>To share it you can post it this forum.</p>"},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/shadertoggler.html","title":"Shader Toggler","text":""},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/shadertoggler.html#preface","title":"Preface","text":"<p>Okay, let's talk about the basics. You will need the add-on version of ReShade. Read it here.</p>"},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/shadertoggler.html#requirements","title":"Requirements","text":"<p>Then you will need to download the add-on it self: https://github.com/FransBouma/ShaderToggler/releases</p> <p>Make sure you download the correct one for your game.</p> <p></p>"},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/shadertoggler.html#main-tutorial","title":"Main Tutorial","text":"<p>For this Guide we are going to use a Free game that does not let you disable a effect.</p> <p>In this case we are going to use a Free Game called. \"Mimic Search.\"</p> <p>Download it here.</p> <p>Install the game and install ReShade with The Add-on listed above. In this case it's the, <code>ShaderToggler.addon64</code>.</p> <p>Make Sure all other ReShade Shader are OFF. We do not want to get mixed out with ReShade's own shaders.</p>"},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/shadertoggler.html#phase-1","title":"Phase 1","text":"<p>So once you have Both ReShade and the Add-on Installed now we can start using it.</p> <p>First thing you want to do is head over to the add-on Tab:</p> <p></p> <p>I minimized the other add-ons to help make it clearer.</p> <p>Also make sure your in the game and you have a problematic effect like Chromatic Aberration.</p> <p>On the intro page this is effect we are targeting:</p> <p></p> <p>Chromatic Aberration - On</p> <p>You also may want to move ReShade's own menu to the right and press New.</p>"},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/shadertoggler.html#phase-2","title":"Phase 2","text":"<p>The menu will change a little bit. But, all is good. Now you should click on <code>Edit</code>.</p> <p></p> <p>Now you want to Enter the name of the effect or what ever you like.</p> <p>In this example we are going to write out <code>CA 01</code> in the <code>Name Box</code>.</p> <p></p>"},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/shadertoggler.html#phase-3","title":"Phase 3","text":"<p>Now let's set up a shortcut. I like to use <code>Ctrl + 1</code> for the first group. You can enter what ever you like.</p> <p>Click the <code>Shortcut Box</code> and press the shortcut keys now. Press <code>OK</code> now.</p> <p>It should look like this now.</p> <p></p> <p>Here we can set it to \u2611\ufe0f activate at startup or not. It is up too you.</p> <p>Now Press <code>OK</code> again.</p>"},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/shadertoggler.html#phase-4","title":"Phase 4","text":"<p>Now you can click on the <code>Change shaders</code> Button.</p> <p></p> <p>Let it run for a bit.</p> <p>It will look like this when it's running:</p> <p></p> <p>Then it will change to this:</p> <p></p> <p>All is good now we can hunt for Shaders.</p>"},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/shadertoggler.html#navigation-and-saving","title":"Navigation and Saving","text":""},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/shadertoggler.html#phase-1_1","title":"Phase 1","text":"<p>We will need to look at the <code>Num Pad</code> in this case.</p> <ul> <li><code>Keys 1 &amp; 2</code> are Navigation and <code>3</code> is Save for Pixel Shaders</li> <li><code>Keys 4 &amp; 5</code> are Navigation and <code>6</code> is Save for Vertex Shaders</li> <li><code>Keys 7 &amp; 8</code> are Navigation and <code>9</code> is Save for Compute Shades</li> </ul> <p>In this case we will use <code>1</code> and <code>2</code> so we can Hunt for the Shader we want.</p> <p>Once we find and save the shader we where looking for by pressing <code>3</code> in this case. It will look like this:</p> <p></p> <p>Now you can click <code>Done</code>.</p> <p></p> <p>Now press the Shortcut listed for me it is <code>Ctrl + 1</code> to activate it:</p> <p></p> <p>Then the Shader should be disabled in this case.</p> <p>Repeat the process for other shaders in the game.</p> <p>Please Note that not all shaders will be accessible by this tool.</p> <p>You also want to click on the, <code>Save all Toggle Groups</code> Button.</p> <p></p>"},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/shadertoggler.html#phase-2_1","title":"Phase 2","text":"<p>Here is the Save file for this Guide:</p> <pre><code>[General]\nAmountGroups=1\n\n[Group0_VertexShaders]\nAmountHashes=0\n\n[Group0_PixelShaders]\nShaderHash0=3090188387\nAmountHashes=1\n\n[Group0_ComputeShaders]\nAmountHashes=0\n\n[Group0]\nName=CA 01\nToggleKey=822083840\nIsActiveAtStartup=False\n</code></pre> <p>The file will be where the game exe/add-on is.</p> <p>Also here is a image from in game with the effect disabled:</p> <p></p> <p>Chromatic Aberration - Off</p>"},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/shadertoggler.html#conclusion","title":"Conclusion","text":"<p>OK, Now that we are done you can keep in mind that. If there are more shaders to hunt down you can always click New again and add a new group.</p> <p>Good luck and happy Shaders Hunting.</p>"},{"location":"depth3d/basicguides/windpi.html","title":"Game Windows DPI Settings","text":"<p>Blurry Text, Images, Videos, Website &amp; Games.</p> <p>Well it also effects ReShade and Depth3D.</p> <p>This is a basic guide to fix this issue:</p> <p></p> <ol> <li>The basic way to do this is to right click on the game's <code>.exe</code>.</li> <li>Select <code>Properties</code></li> <li>Select the <code>Compatibility</code> tab</li> <li>Click on <code>Change High DPI Settings</code></li> <li>At the Bottom check <code>Override high DPI scaling behavior</code>.</li> <li>Open the Pulldown and pick [Application]</li> </ol> <p>There may be a global way of doing this. But, I'm not sure that it will work the same across all modern Window OS's.</p>"},{"location":"depth3d/hardwareguides/sr.html","title":"Simulated Reality Displays","text":"<p>Once known as Dimenco then was bought out by Leia and they didn't go by the name LeiMenco. But, they are the back end of all the SR Tech that is used now.</p> <p>Main Website: https://www.leiainc.com/</p> <p>Hardware Developers Links:</p> <ul> <li>Acer Spatiallabs</li> <li>ASUS Spatial Vision</li> <li>Sony Spatial Reality</li> </ul> <p>If you know more Please Tell me.</p> <p>So this guide is to get SuperDepth3D working on Hardware that has this badge.</p> <p></p>"},{"location":"depth3d/hardwareguides/sr.html#3dgamebridgeprojects","title":"3DGameBridgeProjects","text":"<p>Video Guide</p> <p></p> <p>SuperDepth3D for Simulated Reality Displays.</p>"},{"location":"depth3d/hardwareguides/sr.html#easy-text-guide","title":"Easy Text Guide","text":"<p>Lets install ReShade in the normal way.</p> <ol> <li> <p>Download the add-on version of ReShade.</p> <p></p> </li> <li> <p>Install ReShade by starting the ReShade.exe</p> <p></p> </li> <li> <p>Select or Browse for the games own exe. In this case we are going to install it in to Forza Horizon 4.</p> <p></p> </li> <li> <p>Click <code>Open</code></p> </li> <li> <p>Select the API and next.</p> <p></p> </li> <li> <p>Select Depth3D Repo and Select the Shader. \u2611\ufe0f <code>SuperDepth3D.fx</code></p> <p></p> </li> <li> <p>Next...</p> <p></p> </li> <li> <p>Make sure you pick this add-on. \u2611\ufe0f <code>3DGameBridgeProjects</code></p> <p></p> </li> </ol> <p>Next and Finish.</p>"},{"location":"depth3d/hardwareguides/sr.html#manual-guide","title":"Manual Guide","text":"<ol> <li> <p>Lets install ReShade or Inject ReShade how ever you like. But, make sure it's the Add-on Version of Reshade.</p> <p></p> <p>If it's already Installed Skip this.</p> </li> <li> <p>Now download the latest version of 3DGameBridge.</p> <p></p> </li> <li> <p>Now Copy Both Add-ons or just the one you need based on the game's Arc.</p> <p></p> </li> <li> <p>Now Paste it where ever the games Executable is or where the ReShade's <code>.dll</code> is installed.</p> <p></p> <p>Please start the game and see if it works.</p> </li> </ol>"},{"location":"depth3d/hardwareguides/sr.html#notes","title":"Notes","text":"<p>When you start the game you may need to set your primary monitor to the Simulated Reality Display or the game may not select the correct screen for this to work. It may result with a black screen if you don't do this step.</p> <p></p> <p>Also make sure the game is Native Rez of that 3D Display.</p> <p></p> <p>If the resolution is too small then it will look something like this.</p>"},{"location":"depth3d/hardwareguides/viture.html","title":"VITURE","text":"<p>This Guide is for VITURE Gen 1 Glasses based on what GPU you are running them off.</p> <p></p> <p>VITURE are one of the players when it comes to AR glasses.</p>"},{"location":"depth3d/hardwareguides/viture.html#intel","title":"Intel","text":""},{"location":"depth3d/hardwareguides/viture.html#initial-steps","title":"Initial Steps","text":"<ol> <li> <p>Please Update to your latest Arc Drivers</p> <p></p> </li> <li> <p>Please download this Beta application called Intel Graphics Command Center</p> <p></p> </li> </ol> <p>Plug in your VITURE AR Glasses and switch it in to 3D Mode by Holding down the first button on the glasses for a few sec.</p>"},{"location":"depth3d/hardwareguides/viture.html#instructions","title":"Instructions","text":"<ol> <li> <p>Plug in your VITURE AR Glasses and switch it in to 3D Mode by Holding down the first button on the glasses for a few sec.</p> <p>Under Windows it should look like this:</p> <p></p> <p>It should show up like this as a 3840 x 1080p Screen. If you see this this is good.</p> </li> <li> <p>Start the Intel Graphics Command Center (BETA).</p> <p></p> </li> <li> <p>In here click on <code>Display</code>.</p> <p></p> </li> <li> <p>Now click on the <code>VITURE</code> screen.</p> <p></p> </li> <li> <p>Now go down to setting and change it from your current screen res <code>3840 x 1080</code></p> <p></p> </li> <li> <p>To 1920 x 1080 there.</p> <p></p> </li> <li> <p>Now change your scale size to <code>Stretched</code>.</p> <p></p> </li> <li> <p>That's it and it should look like this.</p> <p></p> </li> </ol> <p>Now Start your game with SuperDepth3D and enjoy your games in Stereo 3D.</p>"},{"location":"depth3d/hardwareguides/viture.html#nvidia","title":"NVIDIA","text":"<ol> <li> <p>First Please Update to your latest Nvidia Drivers.</p> <p></p> </li> <li> <p>Plug in your VITURE AR Glasses and switch it in to <code>3D Mode</code> by Holding down the first button on the glasses for a few sec.</p> <p></p> <p>Under windows it should look like this:</p> <p></p> <p>It should show up like this as a 3840 x 1080p Screen. If you see this this is good.</p> </li> <li> <p>Start the <code>Nvidia Control Panel</code>.</p> <p></p> </li> <li> <p>Once open, click <code>Change Resolution</code>.</p> <p></p> </li> <li> <p>Set it to 1920 x 1080.</p> </li> <li>Good. Now we need to go to the Adjust Desktop size and Position.</li> <li> <p>Make sure you set it to Fullscreen and the rest should default to the correct values.</p> <p></p> </li> <li> <p>Now Start your game with SuperDepth3D and enjoy your games in Stereo 3D.</p> </li> </ol>"}]}